BENIN – The elders of Adesagbon Community have declared that there is no controversy about its origin and status as an autonomous community in Uhunmwode Local Government Area of Edo State. Pa Samuel Osarenkhoe Okungbowa, the Odionwere (Community head) of Adesagbon, in a statement urged concerned authorities to accord the community its deserved honour. He explained that the Adesagbon Community is bounded by six communities of Ehiozevbaru, Iguovbiahianmwen, Obadan, Udeni, Ugha and Okhuo. Part of the statement read, “After thorough investigation and consultation, it is very vital to set the record straight that Adesagbon Community is one of the existing and recognised communities in Uhunmwode Local Government Area of Edo State. “Adesagbon Community is an autonomous Community of its own and it is bounded by six communities of Ehiozevbaru, Iguovbiahianmwen, Obadan, Udeni, Ugha and Okhuo. “It is hereby stated clearly for the notice of the general public that Adesagbon Community is not under the control of these communities mentioned above,” he said.